% ###################### Instructions for Adding Citations ################
%
% - Always ensure each entry includes:
%     • The full title of the paper
%     • The correct journal or conference name
%     • A consistent and informative citation key
%     • Abbreviation from abbr.bib for the book title
%
% - Citation key format: SurnameOfFirstAuthor + Year + MethodAcronym
%   Example: Smith2021nerf
%
% - Each entry MUST include the following metadata fields:
%     • Webpage  – link to the project webpage
%     • Code     – link to the code repository (GitHub, etc.)
%     • Video    – link to the video/demo presentation
%     • Arxiv    – link arxiv *pdf* to later extract thumbnails, etc.
%
%   These metadata fields are crucial for our future website, where we will
%   automatically reuse and display this information.
%
% - Before adding a new entry, always CHECK FOR DUPLICATES.
%   Avoid submitting the same paper under multiple tags or slightly varied names.
%   Use a consistent format and double-check against existing entries.
%
%
% #########################################################################



